{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f8d9650d-d4dd-476b-a36a-dfc320ef43a4","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general migration guide. Here are the key changes:\n\n### 1. **GitHub Actions Workflow**\n\nAdd `id-token: write` permission and replace the `dotnet nuget push` step:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4  # v4+ supports trusted publishing\n\n      - run: dotnet pack --configuration Release\n\n      # Replace your old push step that used secrets.NUGET_API_KEY:\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push \"**/*.nupkg\" --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n        # No --api-key needed — the OIDC token is used automatically\n```\n\nThe critical pieces:\n- **`id-token: write`** permission — lets the runner request an OIDC token\n- **`actions/setup-dotnet@v4`** — v4+ automatically acquires and uses the OIDC token for `dotnet nuget push`\n- **Remove** `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` from your push command\n\n### 2. **NuGet.org Configuration**\n\nOn [nuget.org](https://www.nuget.org):\n1. Go to your account → **API keys** (or package settings)\n2. Navigate to **Trusted Publishers** for your package\n3. Add a trusted publisher entry matching your GitHub repo/workflow:\n   - **Repository owner** — your GitHub org or username\n   - **Repository name** — your repo name\n   - **Workflow filename** — e.g., `publish.yml`\n   - Optionally restrict to a specific **branch/tag** or **environment**\n\n### 3. **Cleanup**\n\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository **Settings → Secrets** once the new flow works\n- You can also revoke the old API key on nuget.org\n\n### Summary of changes\n\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` in push | No secret needed |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` |\n| Any `setup-dotnet` version | `setup-dotnet@v4+` |\n| N/A | Trusted publisher configured on nuget.org |\n\nWould you like me to update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d325ca6a-874f-4a1b-b054-b69ace489393","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there's no existing workflow file to look at. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to OIDC trusted publishing. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":680,"requestId":"4C03:237CD0:6182D4D:6CBA37F:69EC0EEC"},"id":"e4fa7f29-b6ba-40f6-b9a3-5571311fd660","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:51.587Z","parentId":"d8fc5622-b995-407f-bdf2-35edb48acbf0"}
